{%- comment -%}
  Cookie consent banner (Milestone 11 §3): a bottom-anchored card, dismissed
  permanently once the visitor picks Accept or Decline. Reuses the same
  localStorage-adapter dismissal pattern as announcement-bar.liquid (M1).
  This theme ships no analytics/marketing scripts of its own to actually
  gate — both buttons simply record consent and close the banner; a
  merchant's own tracking snippet (added via Theme Settings > Advanced >
  Custom <head> code) is what would read this stored preference in a real
  deployment.
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="cookie-banner" data-cookie-banner hidden role="dialog" aria-live="polite" aria-label="{{ 'general.cookie_banner.heading' | t }}">
  <div class="cookie-banner__body">
    <p class="cookie-banner__text text-small">{{ 'general.cookie_banner.message' | t }}</p>
    <div class="cookie-banner__actions">
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--secondary btn--small" data-cookie-decline>{{ 'general.cookie_banner.decline' | t }}</button>
      <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary btn--small" data-cookie-accept>{{ 'general.cookie_banner.accept' | t }}</button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
